io.amelia.foundation

Class Foundation

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.amelia.foundation.Foundation

  • public final class Foundation
extends java.lang.Object
    Used for accessing majority of the Foundation API.
    The first call to this class MUST be the thread that will initiate the main loop.

    Your main() should look like this: Foundation.prepare(); ... ImplementedApplication app = new ImplementedApplication(); Foundation.setApplication( app ); ... Foundation.start();

      • start

        public static void start()
                  throws ApplicationException.Error
        Will process the application load based on the information provided by the BaseApplication. Takes Runlevel from INITIALIZATION to RUNNING.

        start() will not return until the main looper quits.

        Throws:
        ApplicationException.Error
